
[1]inadequacy

   INAD'EQUACY, n. [from inadequate.] The quality of being unequal or
   insufficient for a purpose.

   The inadequacy and consequent inefficacy

   of the alleged causes--

   1. Inequality.

   Dr. Price considers this inadequacy of representation as our
   fundamental grievance.

   2. Incompleteness; defectiveness; as the inadequacy of ideas.
